{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01T6xzek7gh2FMKNQztCpDv9","type":"tool_result","content":"69:// It defaults to the OSImageURL provided by the CVO but allows a MC provided OSImageURL to take precedence.\n75:\t// Overall the sort is alphanumerical, but custom pool configuration should take priority.\n76:\t// Generally speaking if a custom pool is created, the expectation is that custom pool configuration should override base\n127:\t\t// set for a file and the next iteration overrides the file content but without compression.\n131:\t\t// The empty value will always override the last compression algorithm set in previous merges. After the\n154:\t// Setting FIPS to true or kernelType to a non-default value in any MachineConfig takes priority in setting that field\n156:\t\tif cfg.Spec.FIPS {\n159:\t\tif cfg.Spec.KernelType == KernelTypeRealtime || cfg.Spec.KernelType == KernelType64kPages {\n160:\t\t\tkernelType = cfg.Spec.KernelType\n166:\t\tkernelType = KernelTypeDefault\n171:\t\tkargs = append(kargs, cfg.Spec.KernelArguments...)\n176:\t\textensions = append(extensions, cfg.Spec.Extensions...)\n180:\tif kernelType != KernelTypeDefault {\n186:\t// For layering, we want to let the user override OSImageURL again\n188:\t// so the only way we get an override here is if the user adds something different\n195:\t\tif cfg.Spec.OSImageURL != \"\" {\n196:\t\t\tosImageURL = cfg.Spec.OSImageURL\n201:\tbaseOSExtensionsContainerImage := GetBaseExtensionsImageContainer(&cconfig.Spec, imageStream)\n207:\t\tif cfg.Spec.BaseOSExtensionsContainerImage != \"\" {\n208:\t\t\tbaseOSExtensionsContainerImage = cfg.Spec.BaseOSExtensionsContainerImage\n214:\t\t\tOSImageURL:                     osImageURL,\n215:\t\t\tBaseOSExtensionsContainerImage: baseOSExtensionsContainerImage,\n216:\t\t\tKernelArguments:                kargs,\n220:\t\t\tFIPS:       fips,\n221:\t\t\tKernelType: kernelType,\n222:\t\t\tExtensions: extensions,\n350:// want to allow MachineConfig objects which just have e.g. KernelArguments\n448:\tif !(cfg.KernelType == \"\" || cfg.KernelType == KernelTypeDefault || cfg.KernelType == KernelTypeRealtime || cfg.KernelType == KernelType64kPages) {\n449:\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"kernelType=%s is invalid\", cfg.KernelType)\n461:\t\tif len(cfg.Extensions) > 0 {\n462:\t\t\tif err := ValidateMachineConfigExtensions(cfg); err != nil {\n508:func ValidateMachineConfigExtensions(cfg mcfgv1.MachineConfigSpec) error {\n509:\treturn validateExtensions(cfg.Extensions)\n512:func validateExtensions(exts []string) error {\n513:\tsupportedExtensions := SupportedExtensions()\n516:\t\tif _, ok := supportedExtensions[ext]; !ok {\n526:func GetPackagesForSupportedKernelType(kernelType string) (string, map[string][]string, error) {\n528:\t\tKernelTypeDefault:  {\"kernel\", \"kernel-core\", \"kernel-modules\", \"kernel-modules-core\", \"kernel-modules-extra\"},\n529:\t\tKernelTypeRealtime: {\"kernel-rt-core\", \"kernel-rt-modules\", \"kernel-rt-modules-extra\", \"kernel-rt-kvm\"},\n530:\t\tKernelType64kPages: {\"kernel-64k-core\", \"kernel-64k-modules\", \"kernel-64k-modules-core\", \"kernel-64k-modules-extra\"},","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01StZ8bivggpJ9wizKSD3pYH","session_id":"d92bfeb3-c200-4c47-98a5-9b3219bcc18c","uuid":"60624526-cec6-4386-bdc8-4d8e30c11436","timestamp":"2026-06-22T20:58:23.135Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Find MachineConfig merge/render ordering logic"}
